# The credential contract for this repository.
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is git-ignored (.gitignore:26) and this
# example is deliberately NOT (.gitignore:28) — so this file is the only place
# the contract is written down for someone who has just cloned.
#
# `scripts/serve-development.sh` exports every KEY=value line here before
# starting a workload, so a compose `${VAR:-}` interpolation picks it up. The
# caller's environment wins over the file. Lines must be plain KEY=value.
#
# NOTHING ELSE LOADS THIS FILE. A bare `printenv OPENAI_API_KEY` in a shell is
# empty even when the key is configured — that is expected, not a fault, and
# has already been mistaken for a missing key once.
#
# Never commit real values. Never print one, even a prefix: a partial
# credential is still a credential, and the release scan is right to treat a
# pasted token as a leak whether or not it works.

# Development workload ports. The base is the block this repo is allotted; the
# others are derived from it and must not collide with a sibling project's.
WORKAHOLIC_PORT_BASE=4100
WORKAHOLIC_DEV_PORT=4100
WORKAHOLIC_DOCS_PORT=4101

# Voice Q&A over the Realtime API (ticket 20260716095636). OPTIONAL and OFF
# when absent: `npx qfs-viewer` at a repository root must stay true to its
# own pitch — no build step, no database, no central configuration — so the
# product works without this and gains a voice surface with it.
#
# This key MUST NOT reach the browser. The server mints a short-lived ephemeral
# session token and the page gets only that; shipping this value to a page
# would hand it to every visitor of a published host.
OPENAI_API_KEY=
